@vdonato: thanks, that helped; installed `streamlit-nightly 1.20.1.dev20230315`.

@sfc-gh-kbregula: The example from above is now rendered as:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3042273/225562316-ef31f933-befc-4a70-a370-fd917c2a2b16.png)

Thus `st.code()` now seems to trim leading spaces on all lines. The `st.markdown()` works the same way as before :man_shrugging:

I think this would be the function to change?
```
def clean_text(text: "SupportsStr") -> str:
    """Convert an object to text, dedent it, and strip whitespace."""
    return textwrap.dedent(str(text)).strip()
```
